Title: The Nahda Women's Association Collection
صورة من حفل وضع حجر أساس لمركز ذوي الإعاقة، 1970-79
AltTitle.other: A Photograph of a Cornerstone Laying Ceremony for a Centre for Persons with Disabilities, 1970-79
Description.note: A monochrome, taken in the 1970s, shows a moment during a cornerstone ceremony for a centre for people with disabilities, affiliated with al-Nahda Women's Association, in the Israeli-occupied city of Ramallah. The event featured an audience from Ramallah, members of the Association, and a Swedish delegation.  |~|صورة أحاديّة التدرج اللوني من احتفال وضع جحر أساس لمركز لذوي الإعاقة تابع لجمعية النهضة النسائية في رام الله في سبعينيات القرن العشرين. حضر الاحتفال أهالٍ من مدينة رام الله المحتلة إلى جانب عضوات الجمعية ووفدٍ سويدي.
References: Badi'a Khalaf (Chairwoman of the Nahda Women's Association), interview with PMDA researcher Lama Ghosheh, August – September 2018, non-transcript, the Palestinian Museum Digital Archive.
Series & Collection: Nahda Women's Association Sub-collection 1: Photographs | The Nahda Women's Association Collection
Description (Eng): A monochrome, taken in the 1970s, shows a moment during a cornerstone ceremony for a centre for people with disabilities, affiliated with al-Nahda Women's Association, in the Israeli-occupied city of Ramallah.
